<catsoop-subsection>Line of Symmetry</catsoop-subsection>

A **line of symmetry** is an invisible line that splits a shape into two equal parts. When you fold the shape along this line, both sides look the same or overlap perfectly.

*Or*

A line of symmetry is like a mirror line. If you place a mirror on this line, one half of the shape will reflect exactly to make the other half. Both sides look the same, just like a mirror image.

